observationText: The Panc 04.03 cell line was derived from a pancreatic adenocarcinoma and has a mutation in the KRAS oncogene.
Panc 04.03 cells form moderately differentiated adenocarcinomas when injected subcutaneously into nude mice.
The Panc 04.03 cell line exhibits epithelial-like morphology in culture.
Panc 04.03 cells exhibit high expression of the chemokine receptor CXCR4.
Treatment with the CXCR4 antagonist AMD3100 inhibits migration and invasion of Panc 04.03 cells in vitro.
Panc 04.03 cells are resistant to gemcitabine treatment in vitro.
Panc 04.03 cells exhibit high expression of the stem cell marker CD24.
Knockdown of CD24 expression in Panc 04.03 cells reduces their tumorigenic potential in vivo.
Panc 04.03 cells are sensitive to treatment with the Hsp90 inhibitor 17-AAG in vitro.
